## Errors & Mistakes
The previous compact sed was too narrow: it converted only .0 tokens and then unconditionally inserted 10.3a after 10.0a. As the reviewer pointed out, an input like 10.0 10.3 would become 10.0a 10.3a 10.3, leaving a plain 10.3 token and duplicating the intended architecture. The corrected expression handles existing 10.3 by first converting it to 10.3a and only injecting 10.3a when absent.

## Dead Ends
