## Hints for Future Agents
The final intended diff remains SM103-only in vllm-tensorizer/Dockerfile. It should not include removal of ubuntu-toolchain-r apt sources, apt retry flags, or other builder package-management changes. The sed expression intentionally handles both the current base list without 10.3 and a future base list that already includes 10.3 or 10.3a. If a future maintainer edits this line, preserve these cases: current base list -> 8.0 8.9 9.0a 10.0a 10.3a 12.0a; 10.0 10.3 -> 10.0a 10.3a. NVCC_WRAPPER_FILTER_CODES is a denylist and should include plain sm_103/compute_103, not sm_103a/compute_103a.

## Codebase Discoveries
GNU sed address negation can keep the expression compact while avoiding duplicate insertion: /\b10\.3a\b/!s@\b10\.0a\b@10.0a 10.3a@ runs the insertion only if the full line does not already contain 10.3a.

